    "R. Alan Culpepper": "The Departure from Capernaum 1:35-39\nv. 4: they wash \u201ccups, pots, and\nbronze kettles,\u201d and some manuscripts add \u201cand beds\u201d or possibly\n\u201cdining couches\u201d (NIV). If beds were originally included (following\n4. Beasley-Murray is more precise in observing that this\npassage \u201cis less a series of citations than a conflation of allusions\u201d to the\nday of the Lord.41 The citations are not exact, although the allusions\n[v_Isa_13_10] are clear, especially the dependence on Isaiah `[char_Isaiah_Gen_26]` 13:",
